</div><div class="courseblock">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>PHYS 481.  Modern Experimental Physics I.  4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Theory and experimental use of linear circuits, semiconductor devices, amplifiers, oscillators. Techniques and experiments in atomic, molecular and solid-state physics. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20240" title="PHYS 240" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 240');">PHYS 240</a>; or approval of the department. Requires concurrent registration in <a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20499" title="PHYS 499" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 499');">PHYS 499</a> for students enrolled in the BA or BS in Physics programs. Class Schedule Information: To be properly registered, students must enroll in one Laboratory and one Lecture-Discussion.<br/>
