</div><div class="courseblock">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>PHYS 482.  Modern Experimental Physics II.  4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Techniques and experiments in nuclear and particle physics. Gamma-gamma correlations, muon lifetime, Compton scattering, alpha particle scattering. Computer-based experimentation. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=PHYS%20481" title="PHYS 481" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'PHYS 481');">PHYS 481</a>; or approval of the department. Class Schedule Information:  To be properly registered, students must enroll in one Laboratory and one Lecture-Discussion.<br/>
</p>
